 founded in sunnyvale california in  by brothers ken and michael xie the founders had previously served in executive positions at netscreen and servgate respectively the company was initially named appligation inc then renamed to appsecure in december  and later renamed to fortinet based on the phrase fortified networks it spent two years in research and development before introducing its first product in  fortinet raised  million in private funding from  to early  an additional  million in financing was raised in august  followed by  million in march  reaching a total of  million in funding according to fortinet its revenues grew tenfold from  to  its first channel program was established in october  westcon canada started distributing fortigate products in canada in december  which was followed by norwood adam in the uk in february  the reseller program was reorganized in january  and named soc in a box by  fortinet had offices in asia europe and north america in october  a study by opennet found that fortinets appliances were being used for internet censorship in myanmar fortinet said its products are sold by third party resellers and it respects us embargoes however photographs were found of a fortinet salesperson with burmas prime minister legal disputesedit a german linux programmer from gplviolationsorg obtained a preliminary injunction against fortinets uk subsidiary in april  due to allegations that the company was using encryption to hide its use of linux kernels that are subject to a general public license gpl the licenses terms require disclosure of the source code the following month fortinet agreed to make its source code for gpllicensed elements available upon request modified its licensing terms and made other changes ending the dispute in may  trend micro filed a legal complaint against fortinet alleging that its antivirus technology infringed trend micros patents on methods for scanning email and internet traffic that august the international trade commission ruled against fortinet prohibiting the sale of effected products fortinet said trend micros patents were too broad but it complied with the ruling fortinet and trend micro reached an agreement with undisclosed terms in january  and fortinet modified its antivirus products to avoid trend micros patents a few years later an attorney from the international trade commission filed an opinion for another case that said he felt the related patents from trend micro were invalid fortinet made a new legal filing and in december  the us patent and trademark office declared the patents as invalid in december  fortinet sued sophos under allegations that it was poaching fortinet employees and infringing on fortinet patents the legal dispute was settled two years later in mediation with nondisclosed terms further developmentedit in  fortinet researchers said a facebook widget from zango had tricked more than three million users into downloading malicious spyware under the guise of telling users their secret crush zango denied the allegations saying their software was optin in late  fortinet acquired the database security and auditing intellectual property of iplocks and extended job offers to the companys  employees it acquired the intellectual property and other assets of woven systems an ethernet switching company in august  according to idc by this time it was the largest unified threat management vendor with a  percent marketshare the company had been growing steadily and became profitable after losing money from    fortinet was also rising in crn magazines surveybased annual report card arc reaching first place in  in november  fortinet had an initial public offering it was planning to raise  million through the sale of  million shares many stockholders also sold their shares simultaneously just before the first day of trading fortinet increased the share price from  to  and the price increased in the market to  by the end of the first day of trading raising  million in financing recent historyedit by  fortinet had  million in annual revenues that november bloomberg covered rumors that ibm was considering acquiring the company which fortinet denied in december  fortinet acquired xdn formerly known as crowd which provided an apphosting service called crowddirector in  fortinet acquired application delivery company coyote point for an undisclosed sum fortinet made changes to its reseller program in july  in order to provide financing and other options for small managed security service vendors recently some resellers have complained that fortinet is competing with its own resellers whereas fortinet says it does not do any direct sales fortinet founded the cyber threat alliance with palo alto networks in  in order to share security threat data across vendors it was joined by mcafee and symantec later that year in may  fortinet acquired the silicon valleybased wifi hardware company meru networks for  million in late  fortinet security researchers demonstrated a fitbit hack that gained access through bluetooth then allowed the hacker into synchronized devices in june  fortinet acquired an it security monitoring and analytics software vendor accelops for about  million according to zdnet the company was best known for its security information and event management siem products products which analyze hardware and software security alerts productsedit fortinet develops and markets it security and networking hardware and software it is best known for the fortigate family of security appliances which combine many cybersecurity functions according to a  report by it analyst firm the delloro group fortinet had an eight percent marketshare of the it security appliance market by revenue in  up from  percent in  this makes it the fourthlargest vendor in the industry according to fortinet its users are  small businesses  enterprises and  large companies fortigateedit fortinets fortigate family of unified threat management physical and virtual appliances include a number of security functions like firewalls intrusion prevention webfilters and protection from malware or spam the family includes products for small businesses and branch offices as well as for large enterprises data centers and internet service providers it also sells next generation firewalls ngfw which gartner defines as being a product that combines firewall vpn intrusion prevention and other security features fortinets first product was the fortigate  released in october  which had a throughput of  gigabits per second gbits the  family was released two years later according to the international directory of company histories fortinets early products for small businesses and branch offices were well received by the industry in early  fortinet added firewall functionality to the fortigate appliance designed for internal networks and relying on specialpurpose asics the fortigate virtual appliance was later added to the amazon web services in  in april  fortinet announced the fortinet security fabric which is intended to allow thirdparty devices to share information with fortinet appliances and software through apis initial fabricready partners include brocade carbon black centrify nozomi networks palerra pulse secure qualys inc tufin ubiqube verisign inc whitehat security and ziften fortinet also introduced the fortigate e gbits firewall which includes the new cp asic that takes on some processing tasks from the main cpu and was used in future fortigate releases other productsedit fortinet provides numerous other software and hardware products including more than one dozen other products for switching desktops voip services dns user authentication and other applications the companys fortianalyzer software offers reporting features for fortinet products including event logging security reporting and analysis forticlient is an endpoint security product for desktops phones and other devices forticlient vpn software was first released in april  the fortiguard antispam and the fortimail messaging security products were first released in february  fortimanager the companys software for data center security was first introduced in april  fortinet introduced its database security product family in  fortinets fortiswitch switching platforms were first introduced in  and its application delivery controllers in august  in october  fortinet released virtual software versions of its fortigate fortimanager fortianalyzer and fortimail appliances it updated the forticloud management system in august  a softwaredefined networking offering was introduced in september  fortinet produces and markets wireless versions of its fortigate product called fortiwifi which was first in march  fortinet introduced a new family of cloudbased wireless access points in august  the fortiddos product family was introduced in march  fortiguard also provide a visual output of global sample data collected from all fortigate appliances connected to the fortiguard labs databases the threat map is publicly available for sample data and can also be viewed specific to a single fortigate appliance within fortios operationsedit fortinet also runs the fortiguard labs internal security research team which was founded in  it has four research and development centers in asia as well as others in the us canada and france fortinet hosts a certification and training program with eight levels of nse certification it runs the network security academy which was founded in early  it provides resources to universities teaching it security classes referencesedit  a b c d e f fortinet inc annual report k  fortinetcom retrieved april     a b c d e f g h i hill karen  international directory of company historiesfortinet  st james press pp –  accessdate requires url help  a b kenneth tam martín h hoz salvador ken mcalpine rick basile bruce matsugu josh more december   utm security with fortinet mastering fortios newnes pp – isbn    a b natividad beverly march  